-- Poland's CPI expectations inch down to 0.5 pct y/y in March
-- By Marcin Goettig
-- Mon Mar 31, 2014 08:01AM EDT
-- None



WARSAW, March 31 (Reuters) - Polish households' expectations of average inflation over the next 12 months edged down to 0.5 percent on an annual basis in March, the central bank said on Monday.

The central bank at the same time confirmed the figure for February at 0.6 percent.